### STL Algorithms

The `<algorithm>` header provides a comprehensive set of template functions that operate on ranges defined by iterators.

---

### Non-Modifying Algorithms

| Algorithm | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `find(begin, end, value)` | Find first occurrence |
| `count(begin, end, value)` | Count occurrences |
| `equal(begin1, end1, begin2)` | Check equality |
| `search(begin, end, pattern)` | Search for subsequence |
| `all_of`, `any_of`, `none_of` | Range predicates (C++11) |

```cpp
vector<int> v = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
auto it = find(v.begin(), v.end(), 3);
bool hasEven = any_of(v.begin(), v.end(), [](int x) { return x % 2 == 0; });
```

---

### Modifying Algorithms

| Algorithm | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `sort(begin, end)` | Sort ascending |
| `reverse(begin, end)` | Reverse order |
| `copy(from, to)` | Copy elements |
| `fill(begin, end, value)` | Fill with value |
| `transform(in, out, func)` | Apply function |
| `replace(begin, end, old, new)` | Replace values |

---

### Example: sort and transform

```cpp
vector<int> nums = {4, 2, 5, 1, 3};
sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());  // {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}

vector<int> squares(nums.size());
transform(nums.begin(), nums.end(), squares.begin(),
          [](int x) { return x * x; });
```

---

### Numeric Algorithms

```cpp
#include <numeric>

vector<int> v = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
int sum = accumulate(v.begin(), v.end(), 0);        // 15
int product = accumulate(v.begin(), v.end(), 1, multiplies<int>());  // 120
vector<int> partial;  // {1, 3, 6, 10, 15}
partial_sum(v.begin(), v.end(), back_inserter(partial));
```

---

### Custom Comparators

```cpp
// Sort descending
sort(v.begin(), v.end(), greater<int>());

// Sort by custom predicate
sort(v.begin(), v.end(), [](int a, int b) {
  return abs(a) < abs(b);
});
```

---

> **Key Point:** STL algorithms work with ranges defined by iterators. They are efficient, well-tested, and express intent clearly. Prefer them over hand-written loops.

codeExample:
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
#include <numeric>
using namespace std;

int main() {
  vector<int> nums = {3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9, 2, 6};

  sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());

  auto it = unique(nums.begin(), nums.end());
  nums.erase(it, nums.end());

  int sum = accumulate(nums.begin(), nums.end(), 0);
  cout << "Sum: " << sum << endl;

  cout << "Processed: ";
  for (int n : nums) cout << n << " ";
  return 0;
}
